 data-rr-ui-event-key="1" class="nav-link" href="/customizedreport">Customised Report</a><a data-rr-ui-event-key="1" class="nav-link" href="/gemstone">Gemstone</a><a data-rr-ui-event-key="1" class="nav-link" href="/panchang">Panchang</a></div></div></div></nav></div><main><div class="top-banner"><img src="/InsideBanner/Gemology.png"/></div><div class="breadcrum one"><div class="container"><ul><li><a href="/">Home</a></li><li><a href="/gemstone">Gemstone</a></li><li>Ruby Stone or Manik</li></ul></div></div><div class="container page-content  pb-50"><div class="row col-12"><div class="large-leftbox"><div><h1 class="page-heading">Ruby Stone or Manik</h1><img class="featured_image" src="/assets/gemstone/Ruby-Stone-Manik.jpg" alt="Ruby Stone or Manik"/><div><p>The Ruby gemstone, known as 'Manik' in Hindi, is revered for its association with the Sun. This radiant gem is believed to bring success, wealth, and prosperity to the wearer by enhancing the influence of the Sun in their horoscope. Manikya symbolizes power, authority, and vitality. Astrologers often recommend this gem to strengthen one's self-confidence and boost overall well-being. It is said that wearing a Ruby can positively impact the wearer's career, relationships, and health, aligning them with the favorable energies of the Sun.</p><h1>What is Ruby Stone or Manik?</h1><p>Ruby, known as 'Manik' in Sanskrit, is a precious gemstone of the Corundum family. It exhibits a range of red hues, from pinkish to pigeon blood red. Rubies are valued for their hardness, durability, luster, and rarity. They are traditionally associated with the Sun in Vedic astrology.</p><h2>Benefits of Wearing Ruby Stone/ Manik</h2><p>Wearing a Ruby ( Manik ) can have several benefits:</p><ul><li>It is believed to enhance leadership qualities and boost self-confidence.</li><li>Rubies are said to bring fame, vigor, virtue, warmth, and the capacity to command to its wearer.</li><li>They can also aid in health issues, particularly those related to the heart and blood circulation.</li></ul><h2>Who Can Wear Ruby Gemstone?</h2><p>Ruby is beneficial for those with a weak or afflicted Sun in their horoscope. People in leadership roles, administrative services, politics, or the judiciary can benefit from wearing this stone.</p><h2>How to Wear Ruby or Manik Stone</h2><p>To wear a Ruby, follow these guidelines:</p><ul><li>The gemstone should be set in gold or copper and worn on the ring finger.</li><li>The ideal day for wearing Ruby is Sunday morning during the Shukla Paksha (Waxing Moon).</li><li>Cleanse the ring with Ganga Jal or raw milk and chant the Sun mantra: 'ॐ सूर्याय नमः' (Om Suryaya Namah) 108 times before wearing it.</li></ul><h2>Negative Effects of Wearing Ruby Gemstone</h2><p>If worn by an unsuitable zodiac or ascendant, Ruby can cause aggression, conflicts, health issues related to blood and heart, and disturb mental peace.</p><h2>FAQ's</h2><h3>Which Rashi is Suitable Zodiac Signs for Ruby ( Manik)</h3><p>Ruby is especially advantageous for Leo sun sign individuals. However, those with Aries, Sagittarius, Pisces, and Scorpio sun signs can also benefit from wearing this gemstone.</p><h3>Who Should Never Wear a Ruby</h3><p>People with a malefic Sun in their horoscope, particularly Taurus, Libra, Capricorn, and Aquarius sun signs, should avoid wearing Ruby. It could bring negative impacts like health issues and conflicts.</p><h3>What is  Ruby Gemstone Used for?</h3><p>Ruby is worn for strengthening a weak Sun in the horoscope, enhancing leadership qualities, and improving health issues related to the heart and eyes.</p><h3>On which finger Ruby gemstone should be worn</h3><p>Wearing Ruby on the ring finger of the right hand holds significant importance in Vedic astrology. This finger is associated with the Sun, a powerful celestial body representing vitality and authority.</p><h3>How should you take care of Ruby gemstone</h3><p>Keep Ruby away from chemicals and sharp blows. Clean it with a soft cloth and mild soap if needed. Avoid prolonged exposure to extreme heat.</p><h3>What type of Ruby gemstone should be worn?</h3><ul><li>Preferred Metal for Ruby</li><p>Gold is the most auspicious metal for setting a Ruby. However, copper can also be used as an alternative.</p><li>Ideal Weight for Ruby</li><p>The minimum weight of a Ruby should be at least 3 Ratti (approximately 2.73 carats) for effective astrological benefits.</p><li>Best Quality Ruby</li><p>The best quality Rubies are those with minimal inclusions, vibrant red color (pigeon blood preferred), and good transparency. Burmese Ruby is considered the finest quality</p></ul><h3>What are some Alternatives to Ruby Gemstone?</h3><p>Red Garnet and Red Spinel are considered substitutes for Ruby, though they are less powerful.</p><h3>Which Ascendants Should Wear Ruby?</h3><p>Ascendants of Aries, Cancer, Leo, Scorpio, Sagittarius, and Pisces can benefit from wearing Ruby.</p><h3>Which Ascendants Should Never Wear Ruby Gemstone?</h3><p>Taurus, Libra, Capricorn, and Aquarius ascendants should generally avoid wearing Ruby due to the potential adverse effects.</p><h2>Conclusion</h2><p>Ruby, with its majestic hues and astrological significance, is more than just a jewel. It's a cosmic tool that, when worn correctly, can unlock a plethora of benefits</p></div></div></div><div class="small-rightbox"><div class="connect-astrologer"><a href="/astrologers"><div class="content"><i class="fa-solid fa-phone-volume"></i><h3>Connect With Astrologer</h3></div></a></div><div class="banner-info-one"><div class="content"><h2><img src="/ReportsIcon/business-report.png" alt="Business Report"/>Business Report</h2><p>Your detailed personalized Business Report can be the ultimate guide to  understanding ...</p><div class="readmore"><a href="/customizedreport/business-report">Read More</a></div></div></div><div class="banner-info-one"><div class="content"><h2><img src="/ReportsIcon/child-name.png" alt="Child Name Report"/>Child Name Report</h