mstone Used for?\u003c/h3\u003e","\u003cp\u003eRuby is worn for strengthening a weak Sun in the horoscope, enhancing leadership qualities, and improving health issues related to the heart and eyes.\u003c/p\u003e","\u003ch3\u003eOn which finger Ruby gemstone should be worn\u003c/h3\u003e","\u003cp\u003eWearing Ruby on the ring finger of the right hand holds significant importance in Vedic astrology. This finger is associated with the Sun, a powerful celestial body representing vitality and authority.\u003c/p\u003e","\u003ch3\u003eHow should you take care of Ruby gemstone\u003c/h3\u003e","\u003cp\u003eKeep Ruby away from chemicals and sharp blows. Clean it with a soft cloth and mild soap if needed. Avoid prolonged exposure to extreme heat.\u003c/p\u003e","\u003ch3\u003eWhat type of Ruby gemstone should be worn?\u003c/h3\u003e","\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003ePreferred Metal for Ruby\u003c/li\u003e\u003cp\u003eGold is the most auspicious metal for setting a Ruby. However, copper can also be used as an alternative.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cli\u003eIdeal Weight for Ruby\u003c/li\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe minimum weight of a Ruby should be at least 3 Ratti (approximately 2.73 carats) for effective astrological benefits.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cli\u003eBest Quality Ruby\u003c/li\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe best quality Rubies are those with minimal inclusions, vibrant red color (pigeon blood preferred), and good transparency. Burmese Ruby is considered the finest quality\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e","\u003ch3\u003eWhat are some Alternatives to Ruby Gemstone?\u003c/h3\u003e","\u003cp\u003eRed Garnet and Red Spinel are considered substitutes for Ruby, though they are less powerful.\u003c/p\u003e","\u003ch3\u003eWhich Ascendants Should Wear Ruby?\u003c/h3\u003e","\u003cp\u003eAscendants of Aries, Cancer, Leo, Scorpio, Sagittarius, and Pisces can benefit from wearing Ruby.\u003c/p\u003e","\u003ch3\u003eWhich Ascendants Should Never Wear Ruby Gemstone?\u003c/h3\u003e","\u003cp\u003eTaurus, Libra, Capricorn, and Aquarius ascendants should generally avoid wearing Ruby due to the potential adverse effects.\u003c/p\u003e","\u003ch2\u003eConclusion\u003c/h2\u003e","\u003cp\u003eRuby, with its majestic hues and astrological significance, is more than just a jewel. It's a cosmic tool that, when worn correctly, can unlock a plethora of benefits\u003c/p\u003e"]}},"__N_SSP":true},"page":"/gemstone/[slug]","query":{"slug":"benefits-of-ruby-stone"},"buildId":"lsQnun64ZlFUJSJ9KhLc5","isFallback":false,"isExperimentalCompile":false,"gssp":true,"scriptLoader":[]}</script></body></html>